  "about_seo_title": "About",
  "about_seo_desc": "How MeshCore Ninja works — a community-maintained, open-data catalog of MeshCore networks, devices and firmwares, generated from human-readable YAML.",
  "about_intro": "<strong>MeshCore Ninja</strong> is a community-maintained catalogue for the {meshcore} ecosystem — the regional and national {networks} people run, the {devices} that join them, and the {firmwares} that run on them (the reference build plus community forks and custom variants). Each entry carries detailed specs, and a {matrix} shows which firmware supports which hardware at a glance.",
  "about_how_title": "How it works",
  "about_how_p1": "The catalogue is generated at build time from human-readable YAML files in the {dataDir} folder — no database, no server. Records live in collections — {networks}, {devices}, {firmwares} and {vendors} — each a directory of records, where the directory name <em>is</em> the id. A build step compiles them into a single {datajson} the app reads (and which is published for reuse).",
  "about_how_p2": "The one exception is <strong>live network activity</strong> — recent packets, active nodes and observers shown on some network views. That data isn't static: it's gathered and served by an optional realtime collector with its own backing store, and the site only shows it when that service is configured. Everything else works as a plain static site with no backend.",
  "about_contributing_title": "Contributing",
  "about_step_1": "Add or edit a record in the relevant collection, e.g. {networkYaml} or {deviceYaml}.",
  "about_step_2": "Cross-link records by id — a device's {vendorId}, a firmware's {devicesList} list, a network's radio bands, and so on.",
  "about_step_3": "Run {npmTest} to validate against the JSON Schema and referential checks.",
  "about_step_4": "Open a PR.",
  "about_guide": "See {rules} for the authoring guide and {schema} for the full field reference.",
  "about_source_btn": "View the source on GitHub",
  "about_report_btn": "Report an issue",
  "about_accuracy_title": "Accuracy",
  "about_accuracy_p": "Details are gathered from each project's repository and may lag behind the latest release. Corrections via PR are very welcome.",
  "about_licensing_title": "Licensing",
  "about_licensing_p1": "The MeshCore Ninja database — device, firmware, network and compatibility records, schemas, and the generated exports ({datajson}, {devicesjson} and friends) — is dedicated to the public domain under {cc0}, so anyone can embed, sync or re-publish it without attribution. The application source code is licensed under the {mit}.",
  "about_licensing_p2": "Third-party device photographs, vendor logos and trademarks remain the property of their respective owners and are not covered by the CC0 dedication. See the {breakdown} for details.",
